I am puzzled as to why nuclear is seen as any kind of solution. It has a negative learning curve, in other words it consistently becomes more expensive, not less. It requires vast subsidy over decades beyond the most expensive commercial renewables, and it is based on the outdated notion of 'base power'. The future is flexibility through digitisation in the power industry - the tech is leaving one-way power supply from giant stations behind.



